    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-05-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="400" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d400">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Daggett</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 25.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 5,
                                    1883</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Upon the receipt of your No. 63 of the
                                6th ultimo I promptly communicated to the Secretary of the Navy your
                                request touching the presence of a war vessel in the Hawaiian
                                Islands. I have now received Mr. Chandler’s reply, of the 3d
                                instant, in which he states that although his Department will be
                                unable to keep a ship constantly at Honolulu, he has given such
                                directions as will insure one of its vessels visiting that port at
                                as frequent intervals as practicable.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fred’k T.
                                    Frelinghuysen.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
